Recent Progress
This is not a narrative entry, but a piece of reflection.
I've been focused on foundational practice lately. To be honest, I'm feeling quite disorganized right now. I know my fundamentals are weak and need to be strengthened, and I'm also aware that there are still many unpolished parts of the MVP that need work. At the moment, I'm stretched thin trying to keep up with both sides at once.
This feeling isn't anxiety — it's an instinctive sense of chaos, pure and overwhelming chaos.
Every single day, I have to do foundational exercises, work on the next iteration of the MVP, design the overall architecture for the next phase, keep a daily log, review the mistakes I made that day, go over the structural modules of the MVP, and publish sharing posts on several forums...
On top of that, I work 12 hours a day delivering food orders. After setting aside time for meals and showers, I barely have just over three hours of usable time each day. Recently I've stretched it a bit to 4–5 hours, but I can clearly feel that I'm not getting enough rest. Every morning when I wake up, my body feels exhausted and sore all over.
It suddenly occurred to me to ask myself: why am I learning AI? Why do I feel compelled to build the ideas in my head?
Admittedly, part of it is for a good job — a decent, secure life, high income, and respectable social status. But those don't seem to be what I care about most deep down.
Then I wondered if it's some so-called "sense of mission" — an irresistible drive to bring the thoughts in my head into reality. But that doesn't feel quite right either?
As I kept thinking, the image of California kept popping into my mind for no apparent reason. It feels like a yearning for the absolute pinnacle of the world — like I want to truly see what the very top looks like, or perhaps earn the recognition of the people who stand there.
It's strange, hard to put into words. I don't really have an answer. By the logic of a normal person, these kinds of questions should never even cross one's mind, and I can't properly explain it myself.
Maybe human beings are born to drift toward glowing bait.
Or maybe I'm just overthinking everything.
Next Steps
I plan to split my three areas of focus into separate schedules.
Tentatively, I will advance the MVP work on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays, and focus on foundational practice on Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays. On weekends, I will do a comprehensive review of all mistakes from the week, as well as write and publish promotional posts.
I will try this plan first and see how it works out.
Besides that, I would like to sincerely ask for everyone's input. I don't have anyone in the same industry around me, and it's hard to find people in a similar situation online. I don't know if my schedule is reasonable, nor do I know if it's normal to have these unusual thoughts — even though I can't stop myself from having them.
